						<summary>

						<p>Stone built into the wall of the Hirēmaṭha.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is a fragmentary inscription. Only a part of grant portion is preserved. Mentions Chāvuṇḍamayya-nāya[ka], the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> and the [Hundred] and Twenty <hi rend="italic">[mahājanas].</hi> The characters belong to about 12th century A.D.</p>						

